    <!-- ââ BIOGRAPHY ââ -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="section-heading">Biography</h2>
      <div class="bio-text">
        <p>
          Cheng LONG is an Associate Professor at the College of Computing and Data Science (CCDS),
          Nanyang Technological University (NTU), Singapore. He received his PhD from the Hong Kong University of Science
          and Technology (HKUST) in 2015.
        </p>
        <p>
          His research spans <strong>databases</strong> and <strong>machine learning</strong>, with
          a current focus on <strong>vector databases</strong> (for supporting AI applications such as RAG, LLM inference, and agent memory) and <strong>machine learning</strong> and <strong>data management/mining</strong> on spatial data, time series, and graphs. He leads the
          <a href="https://vectordb-ntu.github.io/"><strong>VectorDB @NTU</strong></a> group.
          See <a href="./pages/publications.html"><strong>Publications</strong></a> for more details of his research.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

